MOST IMMEDIATE
No. 1/34/1/2004-Cab.
GOVERNMENT OF INDIA (BHARAT SARKAR)
CABINET SECRETARIAT (MANTRIMANDAL SACHIVALAYA)
New Delhi, the 25th May, 2004
4 Jyaistha, 1926 (S).
The undersigned is directed to say that with effect from the 25" May, 2004 :-
Shri K. Chandra Shekhar Rao relinquished the charge of the office of
Minister of Shipping and assumed the charge of the office of Minister
Without Portfolio;
i)
ii)
Shri T.R. Baalu assumed the charge of the office of Minister of
Shipping. He will continue to hold the charge of the office of Minister of
Road Transport and Highways;
iii)
Shri Taslimuddin relinquished the charge of the office of Minister of
State in the Ministry of Heavy Industries and Public Enterprises and
assumed the charge of the office of Minister of State in the Ministry of
Agriculture and Minister of State in the Ministry of Consumer Affairs,
Food & Public Distribution;
Shri S.S. Palanimanickam relinquished the charge of the office of
Minister of State in the Ministry of Commerce & Industry and assumed
the charge of the office of Minister of State in the Ministry of Finance;
and
iv)
Shri E.V.K.S. Elangovan relinquished the charge of the office of
Minister of State in the Ministry of Petroleum and Natural Gas and
assumed the charge of the office of Minister of State in the Ministry of
Commerce & Industry.
v)
fum.
(K.L. Sharma)
